						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">i'm not sure why i should write 0xC0 to $4017?</div><br /><br />It selects the source of the IRQs I believe.  There's also frame IRQs (which I've never understood the usefulness of), DMC IRQ, and external IRQs (from cart).<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">frantik wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">hmm I just discovered mmc5 has 8 bit PCM output... perhaps that would be the best mapper to use  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_idea.gif" alt=":idea:" title="Idea" /></div>
<br />
<br />Probably shouldn't, you'd have to modify the NES to hear the sound and MMC5 is also one of the rarest mappers.  The sound output is the same as the NES I believe ($5011 register instead of $4011), so if it's 7-bit and you use both of those channels I guess you would have 14-bit sound.  If the extra quality is worth the hassle, depends on what you want to do with it.</div>

