						<div class="postbody">1 second / (44100 bytes / 16 kilobytes) in ms is about 370 ms.. that is plenty of time for drum samples.. if each eighth note hit is 370ms, the BPM would be about 80 bpm.
<br />
<br />edit:  woot got PCM going.. right now it sounds a little faster than 44100 but all i'm doing is counting and looping.  
<br />
<br />looking at mappers i think MMC3 might make the most sense.. i'll load the PCM into $8000 and $A000 and leave the program code in $C000
<br />
<br />edit2:  used UNROM instead for right now.. it's working which is pretty cool actually <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /></div>

